ce:section.ce:para:
The ZIF-8(In) was placed in a quartz boat and calcined at 550 ℃ for 2 h in a tubular furnace with a temperature rise rate of 2 ℃/min in air. The derivant of ZIF-8(In) (DZIF-8(In

                           )
                        ) obtained after cooling to room temperature is ZnO/In2O3.

1, 2, 3 mL of 1.5 mg/L CDs ethanol solutions were added to 100 mL of 3 mg/L DZIF-8(In

                           )
                         aqueous solution. Then the mixed solution was heated and stirred at 60 ℃ for 5 h to obtain a series of CDs@DZIF-8(In

                           )
                        , which are denoted as 1-CDs@DZIF-8(In

                           )
                        , 2-CDs@DZIF-8(In

                           )
                         and 3-CDs@DZIF-8(In

                           )
                        , respectively.
